# DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself) Rules
- Avoid code duplication in all forms
- Extract repeated logic into reusable functions/components
- Use inheritance, composition, and abstraction when appropriate
- When you see similar code in 3+ places, it's time to refactor
- Examples of what to look for:
  - Similar function implementations
  - Repeated validation logic
  - Duplicate configuration settings
  - Copy-pasted UI components
  - Similar test setups